The paper focuses on predicting the popularity of news articles using social media data from Twitter. This involves analyzing users' involvement and reactions towards an article. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
